1. How to change time slots for 'timed class groups'?
On alidcscom026:
cdult
cd v/vme/ctp_proxy
edit cfg2part.c
look for line: clg_ (it is line 465):

int clg_defaults[MAXCLASSGROUPS]= {0,1,1,1,1,1,6,7,8,9};  

edit this line according to needed time slots for each class group.
The setting above means:
classgroup active_time [secs]
0          always active
1          1
2          1
3          1
4          1
5          1
6          6
7          7
8          8
9          9

Save file, compile ctpproxy:
make

Restart ctpproxy (make sure no global run is active when restarting ctpproxy):
alidcsvme001> ctpproxy restart

